<main>
  <div class="hero-section">
    <div class="project-tag-row">
      <span class="tag red">Emergency Alert</span>
      <span class="tag">GPS</span>
      <span class="tag">GSM</span>
      <span class="tag">Embedded C</span>
      <span class="tag">Mini Project</span>
    </div>
    <h1>Accident Detection<br><span>&amp; Alert System</span></h1>
    <p class="subtitle">An automated system that detects vehicle collisions using sensors and instantly sends GPS-based emergency alerts via GSM to saved contacts — potentially life-saving.</p>
  </div>

  <img src="accident.jpg" alt="Accident Detection System" class="project-img" onerror="this.style.display='none';document.getElementById('img-fallback-2').style.display='flex'">
  <div id="img-fallback-2" class="project-img-fallback" style="display:none">🚨</div>

  <div class="section-block">
    <h2>Project Overview</h2>
    <p>This mini project addresses a critical real-world problem — road accidents often result in delayed emergency responses because victims cannot call for help. This system automates the entire process of detecting an accident and alerting emergency contacts.</p>
    <p>The system uses accelerometer and impact sensors to identify collision events. When an accident is detected, it immediately retrieves the vehicle's location via GPS and sends an SMS with coordinates to pre-configured emergency contacts using a GSM module.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section-block">
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <div class="flow-steps">
      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-step-line">
          <div class="dot">1</div>
          <div class="line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-content">
          <h3>Collision Detection</h3>
          <p>Impact and accelerometer sensors continuously monitor for sudden changes in velocity or force indicative of a collision.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-step-line">
          <div class="dot">2</div>
          <div class="line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-content">
          <h3>GPS Location Retrieval</h3>
          <p>The GPS module fetches real-time latitude and longitude coordinates of the vehicle's current location.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-step-line">
          <div class="dot">3</div>
          <div class="line"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-content">
          <h3>GSM Alert Transmission</h3>
          <p>The GSM module sends an SMS to emergency contacts with GPS coordinates and an alert message.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-step-line">
          <div class="dot">4</div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-content">
          <h3>Emergency Response</h3>
          <p>Contacts receive the alert and can dispatch emergency services to the exact GPS location.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-block">
    <h2>Key Features</h2>
    <div class="feature-grid">
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="icon">📍</div>
        <h3>Real-time GPS Tracking</h3>
        <p>Precise location data sent instantly when an accident is detected.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="icon">📱</div>
        <h3>Instant SMS Alert</h3>
        <p>Automatic SMS notifications to emergency contacts via GSM network.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="icon">⚡</div>
        <h3>Auto Detection</h3>
        <p>No manual intervention needed — system reacts in milliseconds.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="icon">🔋</div>
        <h3>Low Power Design</h3>
        <p>Embedded system optimized for continuous operation in vehicles.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-block">
    <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
    <div class="tech-row">
      <span class="tag">Embedded C</span>
      <span class="tag">GPS Module (NEO-6M)</span>
      <span class="tag">GSM Module (SIM800L)</span>
      <span class="tag">Accelerometer</span>
      <span class="tag">Arduino / Microcontroller</span>
      <span class="tag">AT Commands</span>
      <span class="tag">UART Communication</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section-block">
    <h2>What I Learned</h2>
    <div class="outcomes">
      <div class="outcome-item"><i class="fa-solid fa-check-circle"></i><span>GPS module interfacing and NMEA data parsing for location extraction</span></div>
      <div class="outcome-item"><i class="fa-solid fa-check-circle"></i><span>GSM AT command programming for SMS transmission</span></div>
      <div class="outcome-item"><i class="fa-solid fa-check-circle"></i><span>UART serial communication between multiple embedded modules</span></div>
      <div class="outcome-item"><i class="fa-solid fa-check-circle"></i><span>Real-world embedded system problem-solving and debugging</span></div>
      <div class="outcome-item"><i class="fa-solid fa-check-circle"></i><span>Building safety-critical systems with reliability requirements</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="cta-row">
    <a href="https://github.com/arunkumar7950" target="_blank" class="btn-primary"><i class="fa-brands fa-github"></i> View on GitHub</a>
    <a href="index.html" class="btn-outline"><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-left"></i> Back to Portfolio</a>
  </div>

  <div class="nav-projects">
    <a href="project-robot.html" class="nav-proj-link"><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-left"></i> Surveillance Robot</a>
    <span style="color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;align-self:center">Other Projects</span>
    <a href="project-ai.html" class="nav-proj-link">AI Tools Web App <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
  </div>
</main>
